            <div class="card">
                <div class="card-header fw-semibold"><i class="fa-solid fa-signature me-2"></i>Filename obfuscation</div>
                <div class="card-body">
                    <p class="text-body-secondary small mb-4">
                        Every file is stored under a tenant-isolated, random-suffixed key, so names never collide and can't be guessed by counting.
                        <strong>Obfuscate&nbsp;=&nbsp;Yes</strong> uses a fully random name — nothing about the original filename appears anywhere.
                        <strong>Obfuscate&nbsp;=&nbsp;No</strong> keeps a readable, slugified version of the original name in the storage path and URL
                        (friendlier for SEO and recognizable links), e.g. <code>annual-report-a1b2c3d4.pdf</code>. This applies to <em>new</em> uploads;
                        existing files keep their names.
                    </p>
                    <div class="mb-4">
